    {
      "href": "/comixzombie/list/elevated-horror/",
      "user": "comixzombie",
      "slug": "elevated-horror",
      "title": "“Elevated” Horror",
      "desc": "I think elevated horror is a silly, vague term people like to give a lot of recent horror films to make them seem more \"respectable\".\n\nAnyway, here's a list of all sorts of horror films of varying decade and quality that I have paired up with modern horror films that the internet seems to consider \"elevated\". Some are paired up because of similar themes, some similar plots, and others because the new film feels like it could almost be a remake of the older film. \n\nI really hope this list helps people discover some older horror films they may not have heard of or encourages them to watch one they hadn't gotten around to yet. I had some more obvious options for some of these that I tried to avoid because they just seemed too well known for my liking. Basically, I wanted to avoid mentioning The People Under the Stairs or C.H.U.D. in relation to Jordan Peele's films.",
      "owner": "List by Brad Duncan PATRON",
      "tags": [
        "elevated-horror"
      ]
